{
  "text": "In the nonhomogeneous case g(x) ≡ 0, we improve the existence result established by Wang, Ma and Wang [CITATION_1] since we relax condition (V ) by (V), skip (V ) and recover compactness by the different requirement ( f 2 ) involving r weights. Furthermore, we do not impose any sign condition on g. ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "56395042"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "56395042": {
      "title": "On the existence of solutions for nonhomogeneous Schrödinger-Poisson systems",
      "abstract": "In this paper, we study the existence of solutions for the following nonhomogeneous Schrodinger-Poisson systems: ::: ::: $$ (*) \\quad \\textstyle\\begin{cases} -\\Delta u +V(x)u+K(x)\\phi(x)u =f(x,u)+g(x), &x\\in\\mathbb{R}^{3}, \\\\ -\\Delta\\phi=K(x)u^{2}, \\qquad \\lim_{|x|\\rightarrow+\\infty}\\phi(x)=0, & x\\in\\mathbb{R}^{3}, \\end{cases} $$ ::: ::: where \\(f(x,u)\\) is either sublinear in u as \\(|u|\\rightarrow\\infty\\) or a combination of concave and convex terms. Under some suitable assumptions, the existence of solutions is proved by using critical point theory."
    }
  }
}